<subSubSection lastPageId="221" lastPageNumber="222" pageId="220" pageNumber="221" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="220.[151,1437,1122,2011]" lastBlockId="221.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="221" lastPageNumber="222" pageId="220" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1806,1831]" pageId="220" pageNumber="221">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1959" box="[667,786,1806,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="220" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis box="[667,786,1806,1831]" italics="true" pageId="220" pageNumber="221">A. laticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the body with darkish green reflection and the metapectal-propodeal disc black; the clypeus with the anterior margin angulate, without an apical median tooth and with the clypeal carina higher than frons level; the frons without a frontal line; the frontal angle of the ocellar triangle acute; the ocelli large; the metapostnotum without a longitudinal ridge; the metapostnotal-propodeal suture; and the mesopleuron with mesopleural fovea opened, and the mesopleural suture opened with the posterior fovea absent, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1959" box="[405,524,1986,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="220" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis box="[405,524,1986,2011]" italics="true" pageId="220" pageNumber="221">A. laticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the body black; the clypeus with the anterior margin rounded, with an apical median tooth, and with the clypeal carina lower than frons level; the frons with a frontal line; the frontal angle of the ocellar triangle obtuse; the ocelli small; the metapostnotum with a longitudinal ridge; the metapostnotalpropodeal suture convergent to the first pair of metapostnotal carinae; and the mesopleuron with mesopleural fovea closed, and the mesopleural suture closed and the posterior fovea present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
